Fixes #34316

Enables contributed injection grammars to specify an embedded language for their injection targets:

```json
"grammars": [
  {
	"scopeName": "meta.embedded.css",
	"path": "./syntaxes/injection.json",
	"injectTo": [
	  "source.js",
	  "source.ts"
	],
	"embeddedLanguages": {
	  "meta.embedded.css": "css"
	}
  }
]
```

In this example, the `source.js` and `source.ts` scopes now have `css` registered as an embedded language registered for the `"meta.embedded.css"` scope

**Problem**
I'm trying to write an injection for css grammar into JS/TS template strings. The following injection works, the `embeddedLanguages` property does not seem to be observed for injections

```json
    "grammars": [
      {
        "scopeName": "meta.embedded.css",
        "path": "./syntaxes/injection.json",
        "injectTo": [
          "source.js",
          "source.jsx",
          "source.ts",
          "source.tsx"
        ],
        "embeddedLanguages": {
          "meta.embedded.css": "css"
        }
      }
    ]
```

With this in `settings.json`
```json
"files.exclude": {
    "**/*.js": {
      "when": "$(basename).ts"
    }
  },
```
which excludes *.js nera *.ts from file tree in explorer, text SEARCH (via right pane) doesn't search in *.js files at all:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/736697/30388539-73fa6fae-98c9-11e7-8727-2f0ffe406bfb.png)

if remove this setting:
